these feelings,

00:04:00.657 --> 00:04:02.951 position:50% align:center
but you're kind of unsure
what they mean.

00:04:03.034 --> 00:04:05.829 position:50% align:center
How do you find confidence
in what you feel?

00:04:05.912 --> 00:04:07.789 position:50% align:center
Confidence, you say?

00:04:08.748 --> 00:04:10.834 position:50% align:center
--Go on and shuffle the cards.
--Okay.

00:04:10.917 --> 00:04:12.836 position:50% align:center
Now shuffle the other way,
and while you do,

00:04:12.919 --> 00:04:16.881 position:50% align:center
I want you to concentrate on
your desire for confidence.

00:04:16.965 --> 00:04:20.468 position:50% align:center
Good. Now, pick up
whatever card calls out to you.

00:04:20.552 --> 00:04:21.928 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
Here goes.

00:04:24.264 --> 00:04:28.476 position:50% align:center
This card can be read
to mean persistence.

00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:30.645 position:50% align:center
Persistence, huh?

00:04:30.729 --> 00:04:32.439 position:50% align:center
[HANZAWA] Perhaps you've been
trying out some new things

00:04:32.522 --> 00:04:35.150 position:50% align:center
lately in order to bolster
your confidence?

00:04:37.027 --> 00:04:39.237 position:50% align:center
[HANZAWA]
Does that resonate with you?

00:04:42.073 --> 00:04:45.368 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO] The thing is,
I do lack confidence,

00:04:45.452 --> 00:04:47.078 position:50% align:center
but I'm more afraid of
proceeding anyway

00:04:47.162 --> 00:04:49.664 position:50% align:center
and then finding out
I was wrong.

00:04:49.748 --> 00:04:53.126 position:50% align:center
[laughs] You're an
earnest person.

00:04:53.209 --> 00:04:54.711 position:50% align:center
Perhaps after I've graduated,

00:04:54.794 --> 00:04:57.464 position:50% align:center
you'd be a good replacement as
Disciplinary Committee Chairman.

00:04:57.547 --> 00:04:58.631 position:50% align:center
No thanks, I'll pass.

00:04:58.715 --> 00:05:01.009 position:50% align:center
[HANZAWA chuckles]
That was fast.

00:05:01.092 --> 00:05:02.218 position:50% align:center
It seems like you're able to

00:05:02.302 --> 00:05:05.221 position:50% align:center
express your feelings
in other areas.

00:05:05.305 --> 00:05:08.683 position:50% align:center
So, if this is the thing
you're struggling with,

00:05:08.767 --> 00:05:09.976 position:50% align:center
tthen there's
a chance it's because

00:05:10.060 --> 00:05:11.436 position:50% align:center
you've begun to
look at the world

00:05:11.519 --> 00:05:14.105 position:50% align:center
differently than
you ever have before.

00:05:15.774 --> 00:05:17.859 position:50% align:center
[HANZAWA] And to me,
that demonstrates just how

00:05:17.942 --> 00:05:20.862 position:50% align:center
important this particular
issue is to you.

00:05:23.365 --> 00:05:24.991 position:50% align:center
[HANZAWA] So, I think
it's perfectly natural for

00:05:25.075 --> 00:05:27.494 position:50% align:center
your confidence
to be a bit shaken.

00:05:27.577 --> 00:05:29.204 position:50% align:center
But the finish line is close.

00:05:29.287 --> 00:05:32.248 position:50% align:center
I'm sure you can see it just
ahead of you, can't you?

00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:34.459 position:50% align:center
So, don't give up.

00:05:35.627 --> 00:05:38.046 position:50% align:center
Keep on moving forward, okay?

00:05:38.129 --> 00:05:39.422 position:50% align:center
I will!

00:05:39.506 --> 00:05:43.009 position:50% align:center
That's it for now.
I hope it was helpful to you.

00:05:43.093 --> 00:05:44.719 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
Thanks a lot, Chairman.

00:05:50.183 --> 00:05:52.894 position:50% align:center
[HANZAWA]
In terms of romance, it means...

00:05:53.978 --> 00:05:57.315 position:50% align:center
...a love that slowly
blossoms over time.

00:05:57.399 --> 00:05:59.359 position:50% align:center
Ooh, poetic!

00:06:00.402 --> 00:06:04.197 position:50% align:center
I hope it all
works out for Miyano,

00:06:04.280 --> 00:06:06.408 position:50% align:center
but it's a two-way street.

00:06:06.491 --> 00:06:10.203 position:50% align:center
Now then, I probably need to
decide what I'm going to do.

00:06:13.039 --> 00:06:15.750 position:50% align:center
[HANZAWA] Accept my
big brother's situation?

00:06:17.419 --> 00:06:18.712 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:06:21.214 --> 00:06:22.590 position:50% align:center
[HANZAWA]
All right.

00:06:23.508 --> 00:06:25.218 position:50% align:center
--Thanks, that was awesome.
--See ya later, Hirano.

00:06:25.301 --> 00:06:27.137 position:50% align:center
[HIRANO]
Yeah, beat it!

00:06:27.220 --> 00:06:29.097 position:50% align:center
[KURESAWA]
You said you had plans, right?

00:06:29.180 --> 00:06:30.473 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
Yeah.

00:06:30.557 --> 00:06:32.475 position:50% align:center
[KURESAWA] 'Kay, see you
at the competition, then.

00:06:32.559 --> 00:06:35.061 position:50% align:center
[HIRANO]
Sasaki. Your shift is over.

00:06:35.145 --> 00:06:36.646 position:50% align:center
Seems kind of early.

00:06:36.730 --> 00:06:38.565 position:50% align:center
[HIRANO]
Just go and get changed.

00:06:38.648 --> 00:06:40.859 position:50% align:center
Right. I'm finishing up, Mya.

00:06:40.942 --> 00:06:42.902 position:50% align:center
